  "title": "fix(routing): enforce RoutingManager is the last widget",
  "body": "fix #3148\r\n\r\nSee the issue for more context.\r\n\r\nThose widgets can't be added back in IS.js:\r\n - [toggle](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?widgets=unmount&selectedStory=Toggle.default)\r\n - [starRating](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?widgets=unmount&selectedStory=StarRating.default)\r\n - [menu](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?widgets=unmount&selectedStory=Menu.default)\r\n\r\nBut they can with this patch.\r\n - [toggle](https://deploy-preview-3149--algolia-instantsearch.netlify.com/v2/dev-novel/?widgets=unmount&selectedStory=Toggle.default)\r\n - [starRating](https://deploy-preview-3149--algolia-instantsearch.netlify.com/v2/dev-novel/?widgets=unmount&selectedStory=StarRating.default)\r\n - [menu](https://deploy-preview-3149--algolia-instantsearch.netlify.com/v2/dev-novel/?widgets=unmount&selectedStory=Menu.default)\r\n\r\n\r\nThe underlying reason is that the router needs to have a complete state before going through its own `getConfiguration` because it will iterate over all the widgets which expects to have their own `getConfiguration` called first.",
